data: {"text":"**Investigating file creation issues**\n\nI\u2019m finding it interesting that Python created a file, but then an \u0060ls\u0060 command shows it doesn\u2019t exist. Maybe there\u0027s a problem with truncated output, as it returned just the path without errors. The initial command \u0060ls -l /mnt/data\u0060 shows a total of 0, while the second command prints the file\u0027s path successfully. It\u2019s possible the file was created in a different path or environment due to a missing library. I should check the list again.","type":"response.reasoning_summary_text.done","item_id":"rs_0c0cf7e80f86c7640169eb8fb2680c819189ae8b3f8e534658","content_index":0,"output_index":3,"sequence_number":190}

